data.title: Don't waste your time
data.text: We have ordered from Nicks several times now, always disappointed. Literally the worse pizza I have ever ordered in my life. They NEVER cook it well done as requested, and it is obvious that the ingredients they use are NOT fresh. If you want under cooked, greasy pizza, then this the perfect place for you! Don't waste your time or money, we gave them more chances then they deserved.

data.title: WOW, very surprised.
data.text:
Loved this pizza, it was delicious.. Fast delivery while we stayed at a hotel and friendly staff from the phone to delivery guy!  But the food is an A+.. and I know pizza.
Great Job Nick! Keep it up!

data.title: Great location
data.text: The food is great we had a A broccoli and chicken roll and a dinner plate of spaghetti to came with a salad and we had a small bowl of pasta soup for two people split between two people we are so cool and still have plenty of food for tomorrow the staff there is wonderful

data.title: Good food, veryinexpensive
data.text: We happened to be the only ones in the dining room on an early Monday night, but the phone never stopped ringing for people picking up food.  The salads are huge and the garlic rolls delicious!!  I had chicken franchaise and my husband had ziti with broccoli and sausage. The portions are huge and delicious.

data.title: Worst pizza I've ever eaten
data.text: No exaggeration! I've had frozen boxed that was better. Went on a friend's recommendation, but I think we got confused and should have gone to a different Nick's in Boca. This was nothing like what they described. The crust was like cardboard and the toppings were awful. Nothing tasted fresh. The vegetarian portion had broccoli, spinach, green peppers, onions and mushrooms. The mushrooms tasted canned and all the other vegetables tasted like they were frozen and over-boiled before being put on the pizza. They were pale, soggy and yucky. The eggplant portion had little "cardboardy" pieces of breaded eggplant that also tasted like it was processed and from a box, probably previously frozen. We also had salad which was nothing more than a plate full of iceberg lettuce, a tomato wedge or two, and a couple of slices of cucumber with store bought dressing. Unimaginative and not very tasty. I am amazed that other reviewers like the place. So sorry to have to write such a negative review, I usually don't, but it was just that lousy.

data.title: Best pizza in southern Florida
data.text: We are snowbirds who are on an impossible quest to find Florida pizza - and bagels - as good as they are up North.  Nick's Brooklyn Pizza is excellent - the best we have found so far.  We start off with a green salad - they do a very nice job with fresh, crisp lettuce and other salad items.  They cook the pie to our specs - if we ask for a lightly cooked, thin crust, we get it exactly as ordered.  The staff is very friendly and accommodating.  Nick's has a good location off Hillsboro Blvd..  Plenty of street parking.  Nice atmosphere.  Highly recommended.

data.title: Very under impressed
data.text: The service was ok. The place was reasonably clean. The problem was the pizza. I hate to say it but I have had many better. We had toppings of sausage, artichoke and sun dried tomato. The cost for the toppings was $4.00 and they were hard to find. The sausage pieces were no larger than raisins, if that. We could taste the tomatoes, I think, but not see them. The artichokes were just small pieces of leaves. Generally speaking, the pizza had very little taste. On the up side, the garlic rolls were great. Sadly, I can't recommend the place, at least for the pizza.

data.title: Great pizza, give them a try
data.text: Great pizza and very prompt delivery at a fair price.  With all of the chains around the neighborhood, this place trumps them all

data.title: Great place

Great food and unbelievable people.

data.title: Great Delivery
data.text: Ordered from there to the Embassy Suites and were very happy with the food. From NY we are particular with our pizza and were very happy with the results. If we were staying any longer we would have ordered in from there again.

data.text: I've never had an issue with this place when it comes to food. Love the way they do the pizza well done. My issue is with the pace of the delivery...Seems to take awhile to get to your home. Other than that try it out

data.title: Vacation
data.text: This is the place for you ended your family and friends to eat end enjoy delicious food and atmosphere of the best pizza ever you have pasta salads dinners everything taste delicious we are from Michigan we have stayed ate Embassy Suites  anytime we will be at Florida we will visit Nicks Pizza love this place

data.title: Delish!
data.text: We order take out all the time and their Stromboli never fails to impress  and its is THE BEST one i have ever had, it was cooked perfectly and really big the price it is very reasonable too, hubby and I were just absolutely impressed with it.

data.title: Fantastic pizza and pasta, and LIFE-CHANGING tiramisu
data.text:
A hidden gem!  We live nearby and get Nick's carry-out on the regular. The lasagna is very tasty, the pizza is consistently delicious with the dough made fresh in-house, and I love the fact that this place is locally owned and run (not sure if it is all the same family, though it definitely has that vibe).

But the main thing I'd like to talk about here is the tiramisu. I wrestled long and hard with the idea of writing about it as they make it fresh, so when it's gone, it's gone.  However, my desire to see this establishment do well and make even more tiramisu for years to come outweighs my selfish desire to keep this to myself. 

So: this is GAME-CHANGING tiramisu. For $5, you get a huge piece that is so moist, so fresh, the flavours so spot-on, that you will surely be unable to believe your luck and will immediately order a second one. I did not like tiramisu or coffee-flavoured anything (other than actual coffee) before trying Nick's. I am now a convert, and have yet to find tiramisu that I enjoy more than Nick's.

Just one note on location: it is on a quiet road, and I've never felt unsafe at their door at night, but the overall area around this stretch off Hillsboro is not nice. After dark, make sure you drive, do not walk, just to be safe. 

Well done, Nick's, and please keep it coming!

data.title: Nicks Pizza Delivered the Goods
data.text: I was without a car at the Hampton Inn when I heard about Nick's Pizza. The staff seemed to rate them highly, so I called for a delivery. I ordered some mozarella sticks and a thin crust Marguerita pizza. Both were very good. I requested extra dipping sauce for the sticks and they gave me plenty. The drivers were polite and friendly.

data.title: NY Pizza in Deerfield Beach
data.text: We were looking for a pizza place and decided on Nicks when we were visiting the area.  Nicks did not disappoint.  What a great pizza!  NY crust, sausage and mushrooms just like back home.  If you want a great pizza Nicks Is a must.

data.title: Good ...no, GREAT pizza!
data.text: Staying at Hampton Inn in Deerfield.  Long day so tried Nicks delivery for a quick meal.  Fantastic!   Tried the lasagna pizza and we loved it.  Price was right and staff was friendly and on time!!  Try it.  They are good .

data.title: Bummer
data.text: This pizza was recommended by a friend and after checking the web site we went after their supposed opening hours. Sales hours were posted on the entrance but the restaurant was not open. Bummer. Too many pizza choices in the area to go back here.

data.title: Great Pizza
data.text:
Stopped by Nick's Pizza earlier today and loved the pizza. I found this place on my phone and was impressed with the quiet atmosphere and great pizza!
sat outside with my son and they have free parking

data.title: BEST PIZZA IN SOUTH FLORIDA!!!
data.text: A great family place!  Always awesome food and even better people.  If you are looking for great pizza, THIS is the place!!!
